{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"74748c28-3750-4742-88d4-3a919bbe422d","content":"No repo files here, so this is general guidance. Here's how to migrate:\n\n### Key changes\n\n**1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script)**\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test` — you no longer need the VSTest task.\n\n**2. Enable the TRX report logger and code coverage**\n\nPass the flags through `--` (the MTP argument separator):\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*.Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\nOr as a script step (often simpler):\n\n```yaml\n- script: >-\n    dotnet test\n    --configuration Release\n    --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n    --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n```\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage**\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish TRX results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n> For Cobertura output add `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"` or configure it in a `.runsettings` file.\n\n**4. Remove any `<IsTestProject>` / `<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>` workarounds** if they were only needed for VSTest discovery — MTP discovers tests natively via `dotnet test`.\n\n### Summary of what's removed vs. added\n\n| Before (VSTest@3) | After (MTP) |\n|-|-|\n| `VSTest@3` task | `dotnet test` (script or `DotNetCoreCLI@2`) |\n| `.runsettings` for adapter | `--logger trx` + `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` CLI args |\n| Implicit result publishing | Explicit `PublishTestResults@2` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cd9ad724-02bd-4f06-b404-08af36f74633","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty, so this is a general question without a specific codebase. Let me provide guidance on migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform while keeping TRX reports and code coverage.","outputTokens":704,"requestId":"0BC0:1612ED:21CE5F:27BC1A:69F00569"},"id":"62867a0f-ef84-4c89-85af-53b4cc959f41","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:55:20.314Z","parentId":"6c699fcb-ab09-433d-91f2-b4c25f0b3975"}
